# module: eng.uncertainty
# status: internal
# purpose: uncertainty constructors, propagation policy, validation semantics, and uncertainty review vocabulary.
#
# Current implementation:
#   compiler/runtime-recognized internal seeds exist for measured, interval,
#   normal, uniform, ensemble, propagate, uncertainty report metadata, and
#   histogram artifacts.
#
# Target constructor vocabulary:
#   measured(value, std=...)
#   measured(value, error=1 %)
#   interval(lower, upper)
#   normal(mean=..., std=...)
#   uniform(lower, upper)
#   ensemble(source, samples=...)
#   propagate(source, method=linear, ...)
#
# Non-goal:
#   do not promote uncertainty to public support until runtime propagation,
#   review/report artifacts, IDE projection, and tests align.
